The paper proposes significant generalizations to kidney exchange, which involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques to match donors and patients. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories, which are all concerned with algorithmic and optimization problems. Additionally, the paper presents experiments that show improvements in planning and social welfare, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, which are both concerned with empirical evaluations of algorithms and optimization techniques.
